definitionGroups.group: Certain plants with features reminiscent of a human navel.

entries.meaning: Umbilicus spp., especially Umbilicus rupestris), a European perennial succulent herb with round, peltate leaves with a central depression.
Omphalodes spp., with seeds reminiscent of a navel.
Marsh pennywort, herbs of genera Hydrocotyle or Centella.
